examples.en: Her fears were but too too well grounded.
Your accusation must be grounded on facts.
The insurance business is grounded on trust.
If you break that thing, you'll be grounded for a week  no kidding.
I got home at 2 am and Dad grounded me on the spot.
If I catch you smoking again, you're grounded. Do I make myself clear (=used when you are angry)?
A storm grounded the ship on a sandbar.
Lewis' ideas were grounded in his Christian faith.
Let me tell you something  if I catch you kids smoking again, you'll be grounded for a month at least.
For lack of fuel, their planes were grounded.
The fog grounded all aircraft at N. aerodrome.
All applicants must be well grounded in mathematics.
She angrily told his son that if he didn't shape up, he'd be grounded for a month.
All planes were grounded because of poor visibility.
Both boats grounded on a mud bank.
